One thing you may want to do is to have this function accept a callback rather than do the notifications in here (to make it easier to test).


```js
function exportToPDF(filename, cb) {
  ...
  remote.getCurrentWindow().webContents.printToPDF({ printBackground: true }, (error, data) => {
    if (error) {
      cb(error);
    }    
    fs.writeFile(`${filename}.pdf`, data, cb);
```

I meant replacing `basestring` by `text_basestring` from the initial version of the code:

```
def check_type(input, input_type, path = []):
    json_type_map = {
        dict : "Object",
        list: "Array",
        text_basestring: "string",
        }
    if not isinstance(input, input_type):
        raise SituationParsingError(path,
            u"Invalid type: must be of type '{}'.".format(json_type_map[input_type]))
```

